# 1. Abstract

The Smart Book Recommendation & Summarization System is an Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning project developed to recommend books based on their content. The system applies Natural Language Processing (NLP) techniques to analyze book descriptions and recommends similar books using Content-Based Filtering. The project also displays a short summary of the selected book to help users understand the book before reading it.

---

# 2. Introduction

With thousands of books available, users often struggle to find books matching their interests. Traditional search methods rely on keywords and manual browsing, which can be inefficient. This project solves this problem by using machine learning algorithms to recommend books automatically based on textual similarity.

---

# 3. Problem Statement

Finding relevant books from a large collection is difficult and time-consuming. Users require an intelligent recommendation system that can suggest similar books based on their interests and provide a summary for quick understanding.

---

# 4. Objectives

* Develop an AI-based recommendation system.
* Recommend similar books using machine learning.
* Generate a concise summary using book descriptions.
* Build a simple and user-friendly interface using Gradio.

---

# 5. Proposed Solution

The proposed solution uses Content-Based Recommendation. The system converts book descriptions into numerical vectors using TF-IDF Vectorization and calculates similarity using Cosine Similarity. Based on similarity scores, the system recommends the top five books related to the selected book.

